data-triple-N3.o: "Because energy is defined via work, the SI unit for energy is the same as the unit of work the joule (J), named in honour of James Prescott Joule and his experiments on the mechanical equivalent of heat. In slightly more fundamental terms, 1joule is equal to 1newton-metre and, in terms of SI base units: An energy unit that is used in atomic physics, particle physics and high energy physics is the electronvolt (eV). OneeV is equivalent to 1.6021765310J."@en
